WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:05.714
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.881 --> 00:10.886
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:11.053 --> 00:14.431
His name: Merlin.

00:17.100 --> 00:21.688
MORGAUSE: What you are about to do
will bring our enemies to their knees.

00:24.858 --> 00:27.402
-You didn't see their faces?
-They had no faces.

00:28.403 --> 00:29.446
[SHRIEKING]

00:29.613 --> 00:31.490
ARTHUR: What are they?
-The Dorocha.

00:31.657 --> 00:33.450
They are the voices of the dead, my child.

00:33.617 --> 00:36.745
GAIUS: For the tear to be created,
it would have required a blood sacrifice.

00:36.912 --> 00:39.998
To seal it will require another.

00:40.165 --> 00:43.919
If laying down my life will spare the people
of Camelot, then that is what I must do.

00:44.127 --> 00:45.337
[SHRIEKING]

00:46.838 --> 00:48.131
Merlin, no!

01:37.389 --> 01:38.724
We have to get him back to Gaius.

01:39.641 --> 01:42.644
-And abandon the quest?
-He saved my life. I won't let him die.

01:42.811 --> 01:46.940
Sire, if we don't get to the Isle of the Blessed,
hundreds more will perish.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.028
Let me take him.

01:52.279 --> 01:53.614
Carrying a wounded man, alone...

01:53.780 --> 01:56.575
...it'll take you two, three days
to reach Camelot.

01:56.742 --> 01:59.494
Not if I go through
the Valley of the Fallen Kings.

02:02.414 --> 02:04.082
You cannot give up on the quest.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.960
LEON:
Sire, he's right.

02:22.934 --> 02:26.521
This is my fault, and I'm sorry.

02:29.232 --> 02:30.359
Take me with you, please.

02:31.443 --> 02:34.780
-You'll die, Merlin.
-You don't understand. Please, Arthur.

02:35.405 --> 02:37.074
Do you ever do as you're told?

02:37.240 --> 02:39.242
- I have to go with you.
-Merlin.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.244
LANCELOT:
We need to leave.

02:45.874 --> 02:47.417
Go.

03:12.693 --> 03:15.153
[MERLIN GASPING]

03:19.324 --> 03:21.326
[CREATURE SQUAWKS]

03:44.975 --> 03:46.184
[LOUD BUZZING]

03:46.351 --> 03:47.728
Can you hear that?

03:47.894 --> 03:50.230
-Bees?
-Food.

03:52.190 --> 03:56.111
-You trying to get us killed?
-We're riding to our death anyway.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.949
It's good to give the horses a rest.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.452
You're quiet.

04:03.618 --> 04:06.788
That's what happens after three days
listening to Gwaine.

04:07.706 --> 04:09.666
You did the right thing, you know.

04:09.833 --> 04:12.836
-Merlin couldn't have continued with us.
- I should've saved him.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.630
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]
[BUZZING CONTINUES]

04:23.054 --> 04:27.267
If anyone can get Merlin back to Camelot,
Lancelot can.

05:14.648 --> 05:17.400
WOMAN'S VOICE:
Lancelot. Lancelot.

05:20.445 --> 05:22.531
Lancelot.

05:24.783 --> 05:26.910
We bear you no harm.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.912
We wish only to help.

05:30.247 --> 05:31.832
What are you?

05:32.249 --> 05:34.167
We are Vilia.

05:34.584 --> 05:37.671
Spirits of the brooks and streams.

05:38.463 --> 05:42.384
The tear in the veil has upset the balance
of the world.

05:42.926 --> 05:45.679
Good spirits as well as bad roam freely.

05:46.054 --> 05:48.890
But this perilous state
cannot continue for long.

05:51.142 --> 05:53.144
Prince Arthur is riding
to the Isle of the Blessed.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.480
He intends to heal the veil.

05:55.647 --> 05:58.692
He will need help from both of you.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.778
My friend is sick.
| need to get him to Camelot.

06:01.945 --> 06:05.198
Merlin is stronger than
you give him credit for.

06:05.657 --> 06:08.285
The young warlock has great power...

06:08.451 --> 06:11.830
...and a future that has been written
since the dawn of time.

06:11.997 --> 06:13.790
Do not worry.

06:13.957 --> 06:16.459
Even now, my sisters begin to heal him.

06:24.259 --> 06:26.219
You are tired.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.846
You must rest.

06:29.180 --> 06:31.349
| need to find shelter.

06:31.516 --> 06:33.685
VILIA:
You are safe here.

06:34.644 --> 06:35.896
LANCELOT:
The Dorocha.

06:36.396 --> 06:41.026
We will stay with you
and protect you through the night.

07:07.469 --> 07:09.846
ARTHUR: By dawn, we'll be on
the other side of the mountains.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.557
GWAINE:
You can't be serious.

07:12.724 --> 07:14.768
These tunnels are crawling with wilddeoren.

07:14.935 --> 07:17.437
ARTHUR:
These tunnels will take days off our journey.

07:17.604 --> 07:19.230
GWAINE:
If we make it out alive.

07:19.397 --> 07:22.692
-We'll cover ourselves in gaja berries.
-Hah. Sounds great.

07:22.859 --> 07:25.820
It's your choice, Gwaine.
Wilddeoren or Dorocha.

07:26.529 --> 07:28.657
ELYAN: I know which I'd rather go for.
LEON: Me too.

07:32.994 --> 07:35.413
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING IN DISTANCE]

07:47.050 --> 07:49.469
[LOUD SHRIEKING]

07:51.930 --> 07:53.515
Never knew you cared.

07:55.058 --> 07:56.267
[SHRIEKING]

07:56.434 --> 07:57.727
Quick!

08:09.656 --> 08:12.325
PERCIVAL: Remind me again
why we're wearing this disgusting paste.

08:13.076 --> 08:17.497
Wilddeoren are completely blind.
They rely totally on their sense of smell.

08:17.664 --> 08:20.083
Gaja berries will mask our scent.

08:20.250 --> 08:23.378
What are the chances of us getting
through here without seeing a wilddeoren?

08:23.545 --> 08:25.296
None.

08:35.432 --> 08:36.474
[CREATURE SNORTING NEARBY]

08:36.640 --> 08:38.058
Shh.

08:53.783 --> 08:55.702
[SNORTING AND SNIFFING]

08:56.619 --> 08:58.913
[FOOTSTEPS SCRAPING AND THUDDING]

09:07.213 --> 09:09.007
[SNIFFING]

09:09.466 --> 09:10.967
Keep still.

09:12.135 --> 09:13.595
Don't even breathe.

09:14.387 --> 09:16.431
[SHRIEKS]

09:31.237 --> 09:33.323
[WILDDEOREN SNIFFING]

09:39.120 --> 09:40.663
[GRUNTS]

09:44.334 --> 09:46.127
[SNORTING AND SNIFFING]

09:56.846 --> 09:58.598
[SCREAMS]

09:58.973 --> 10:00.892
[THUD]
[WILDDEOREN GROANS]

10:02.477 --> 10:03.603
You fool.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.314
-It's dead.
-That one is, yes.

10:07.732 --> 10:08.858
They hunt in packs.

10:09.025 --> 10:10.777
[WILDDEOREN SQUEALING NEARBY]

10:13.446 --> 10:14.656
Run!

10:18.952 --> 10:20.662
[SQUEALING]

10:24.415 --> 10:26.292
[SHOUTING]

10:31.965 --> 10:33.424
GAIUS:
We need more stretchers.

10:33.591 --> 10:35.635
And sheets, as many sheets as we can find.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.053
Gaius.

10:37.220 --> 10:38.304
[MOB CLAMORING]

10:38.471 --> 10:40.682
The guards were under orders
to shut the gates at dusk.

10:40.849 --> 10:43.685
-Whose orders?
-Lord Agravaine's.

10:45.687 --> 10:48.731
Gaius. Have you come to join us?

10:48.898 --> 10:50.775
Why have you closed the city gates?

10:50.942 --> 10:53.820
We have limited resources, Gaius.

10:53.987 --> 10:57.907
As much as I would like to, we simply
cannot feed and water the entire kingdom.

10:58.074 --> 11:00.243
Surely the people have
a right to be protected.

11:00.410 --> 11:02.871
| would be putting Camelot in danger.

11:03.705 --> 11:06.040
Starvation, disease.

11:07.083 --> 11:09.836
You of all people must understand, Gaius.

11:10.420 --> 11:15.592
The gates will remain shut until
we are free of the evil that plagues us.

11:20.388 --> 11:23.183
-Now, gentlemen, where were we?
-My lords.

11:25.310 --> 11:28.021
May I be granted permission
to address the court?

11:29.939 --> 11:31.274
Guinevere.

11:35.945 --> 11:38.072
Prince Arthur taught me long ago...

11:38.239 --> 11:41.618
...that every citizen of Camelot is important.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.870
He would never stand by
and let them suffer.

11:44.913 --> 11:48.291
He would help them if he could,
and we must do the same.

11:49.417 --> 11:52.003
| feel the pain as much as you.

11:52.170 --> 11:54.005
But we don't have a choice.

11:54.172 --> 11:57.842
If we keep letting people in,
our food will run out within days.

11:58.009 --> 11:59.302
You are wrong.

12:02.639 --> 12:05.892
Perhaps you would enlighten me.

12:07.810 --> 12:11.856
Those outside the gates
are landowners, farmers.

12:12.023 --> 12:15.193
For days, the refugees have been
bartering their wares with the townsfolk...

12:15.360 --> 12:18.404
...in return for the safety of their hearths.

12:18.571 --> 12:21.282
They bring with them
far more than they take.

12:21.491 --> 12:24.160
But how long before these wares run out?

12:26.287 --> 12:32.210
Three days ago, Prince Arthur embarked
on a quest to rid us of these creatures.

12:32.377 --> 12:36.673
At worst, we have another three
before he reaches his goal.

12:38.049 --> 12:40.468
Or do you think he will fail?

12:44.555 --> 12:46.140
Of course not.

12:46.307 --> 12:49.227
Sire, she is right.

12:53.398 --> 12:54.983
Very well.

12:56.067 --> 12:57.777
Reopen the gates.

12:59.946 --> 13:01.197
[CHUCKLES]

13:11.124 --> 13:12.625
Merlin?

13:13.543 --> 13:15.878
-Merlin!
MERLIN: Shh!

13:20.925 --> 13:22.343
Breakfast?

13:22.510 --> 13:24.012
Merlin, what--?

13:25.054 --> 13:26.681
-Why, you--
-What?

13:27.390 --> 13:29.642
You're meant to be dying.

13:29.809 --> 13:31.519
Sorry.

13:31.686 --> 13:33.313
-Here.
-What's that for?

13:33.479 --> 13:35.606
You look like you're going to fall over.

13:37.358 --> 13:39.444
-Yeah, not as quick as Arthur.
-Oh, yeah?

13:40.486 --> 13:42.238
Come on.
We need to catch up with the others.

13:42.405 --> 13:44.532
No, you're going back to Camelot.

13:44.699 --> 13:46.367
-You might be.
-Merlin.

13:46.534 --> 13:48.661
-Say hello to Gaius for me.
-Merlin!

13:52.957 --> 13:55.877
Arthur can't finish this without us.

13:56.044 --> 14:00.006
Arthur's right about you.
You don't ever do as you're told.

14:02.550 --> 14:04.052
No.

14:11.893 --> 14:13.811
They need to rest, sire.

14:14.937 --> 14:16.314
Even Gwaine's gone quiet.

14:18.900 --> 14:21.319
Sounds like a good reason to keep going.

14:33.456 --> 14:34.999
AGRAVAINE:
My lady?

14:40.505 --> 14:42.256
What news of the mighty Camelot?

14:42.423 --> 14:46.135
As we planned.
The city is falling into rack and ruin.

14:46.636 --> 14:48.096
And Arthur?

14:50.306 --> 14:52.683
Last we heard,
he had made it past Daelbeth.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.854
-Will we never be rid of him?
-Patience, my lady.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.774
Even if he makes it to the isle,
the outcome will still be the same.

15:01.234 --> 15:02.777
Then what brings you here so early?

15:06.030 --> 15:07.365
Something's wrong.

15:10.076 --> 15:11.577
A minor irritant.

15:13.871 --> 15:17.083
Guinevere. She takes it upon herself
to speak out against me.

15:18.709 --> 15:21.337
-She's dangerous.
-She's a servant.

15:21.504 --> 15:24.006
A spirited one perhaps,
but a servant nonetheless.

15:24.173 --> 15:25.508
No, you're wrong.

15:25.842 --> 15:29.971
| have dreamt the future, and in I,
that servant sits upon my throne.

15:34.225 --> 15:37.270
| would rather drown in my own blood
than see that day.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.897
Then we must make sure it never comes.

15:40.481 --> 15:42.442
| couldn't agree more.

15:43.276 --> 15:46.320
We must make sure
she never sees another dawn.

15:48.197 --> 15:49.824
Where is Arthur?

15:50.700 --> 15:53.202
-I am unsure.
-Where is he?

15:53.369 --> 15:56.456
-The prince is on a hunting trip, sire.
-When will he be back?

15:56.622 --> 15:58.666
In a few days.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.877
Is there something you need?

16:13.306 --> 16:17.101
Your devotion to the king
is most impressive.

16:18.352 --> 16:20.897
There is something I would like to discuss.

16:22.190 --> 16:23.816
| wish to apologize.

16:23.983 --> 16:26.861
Yesterday, I feel I let the prince down.

16:28.821 --> 16:30.698
| am grateful that you spoke out.

16:30.865 --> 16:34.243
- I did not mean to be discourteous, my lord.
-Well, you weren't.

16:34.410 --> 16:35.995
Not in the least.

16:38.748 --> 16:40.041
Gwen, if you would permit...

16:41.792 --> 16:44.295
...would be grateful to seek your advice.

16:45.213 --> 16:47.089
You understand the people.

16:47.298 --> 16:48.591
I'm not sure I--

16:48.758 --> 16:51.427
If nothing else, I know that
you will be honest with me.

16:54.889 --> 16:57.517
It's not appropriate to talk now, but, um...

16:58.768 --> 17:02.813
...perhaps this evening
you could come to my chambers.

17:04.190 --> 17:06.067
Please, Guinevere. These are dark times.

17:06.233 --> 17:09.403
I'm going to need help
if I'm to guide us through them.

17:11.489 --> 17:13.241
Very well.

17:14.116 --> 17:15.492
Thank you.

17:23.251 --> 17:25.627
-Is everything all right?
-Yes.

17:25.795 --> 17:28.005
He wishes to speak with me later.

17:28.172 --> 17:30.216
| think he means to seek my counsel.

18:04.375 --> 18:05.876
Hello?

18:26.647 --> 18:28.566
We can't stay here.

18:28.941 --> 18:31.152
There's nowhere else, Merlin.

18:33.654 --> 18:37.658
We'll make a fire. It'll keep us safe and dry.

18:39.493 --> 18:42.163
And there's more than enough fuel
to get us through the night.

18:43.205 --> 18:44.665
Here.

18:45.499 --> 18:47.251
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

18:53.674 --> 18:56.218
I'm not entirely useless, you know.

19:15.112 --> 19:18.032
GUARD 1: Get the other side!
GUARD 2: Yes, sir.

19:29.335 --> 19:31.003
GUARD 3:
Halt!

19:43.724 --> 19:46.268
AGRAVAINE:
But do the people feel safe?

19:49.772 --> 19:51.691
You can speak honestly.

19:52.149 --> 19:53.818
No, they do not.

19:54.819 --> 19:56.445
Go on.

19:56.987 --> 19:58.614
They're frightened.

19:59.156 --> 20:01.450
Night after night,
they have seen their friends...

20:01.617 --> 20:04.829
...their parents, their children
all snatched cruelly from them...

20:04.995 --> 20:07.415
...and they don't know who will be next.

20:11.627 --> 20:13.671
What can I do to reassure them?

20:16.924 --> 20:18.008
Show courage.

20:19.802 --> 20:23.097
Shutting the gates last night told them
you were as terrified as they were.

20:24.140 --> 20:25.474
It's like a horse and its rider.

20:25.641 --> 20:28.686
If the people sense your fear,
they will not trust you.

20:29.145 --> 20:30.855
Hmm.

20:31.480 --> 20:34.024
| am grateful for your advice.

20:37.236 --> 20:40.489
You have a wise head
upon your shoulders, Guinevere.

20:54.295 --> 20:57.757
-I have kept you long enough.
-And I must see to the king.

20:58.507 --> 21:02.344
Don't concern yourself with that.
| will ensure he is looked after.

21:02.720 --> 21:04.388
It has been a long day.

21:05.222 --> 21:07.433
I'll have my guards walk you safely home.

21:07.641 --> 21:09.185
Thank you.

21:27.661 --> 21:28.829
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

21:30.664 --> 21:31.957
[SHRIEKS]

21:51.727 --> 21:53.562
Seen anything?

21:54.563 --> 21:56.232
No.

21:56.398 --> 21:59.401
Do you know what we're going to face
on the Isle of the Blessed?

22:02.988 --> 22:04.073
Do you want to tell me?

22:06.492 --> 22:08.953
The burden is mine and mine to bear alone.

22:10.079 --> 22:12.581
Look around, Arthur.

22:13.332 --> 22:17.336
We would fight a thousand armies
with our bare hands for you.

22:18.337 --> 22:20.339
You're never alone.

22:21.882 --> 22:23.509
We stand together.

22:26.720 --> 22:28.138
Come on. I'll take over.

22:29.265 --> 22:30.766
You need some rest.

22:38.023 --> 22:39.650
Thank you.

22:48.701 --> 22:50.786
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING IN DISTANCE]

23:10.139 --> 23:11.682
Gwen?

23:26.113 --> 23:29.491
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING IN DISTANCE]

23:32.578 --> 23:34.079
Gwen?

23:38.292 --> 23:39.668
[SHRIEKING]

24:16.330 --> 24:18.040
[SHRIEKING]

24:27.132 --> 24:30.135
You don't have to continue
on this journey with me, you know.

24:30.302 --> 24:31.887
[CHUCKLES]

24:32.054 --> 24:34.014
Try and stop me.

24:34.515 --> 24:38.727
Why? Because you're a knight,
you feel honor bound?

24:39.645 --> 24:41.438
You wouldn't understand.

24:43.273 --> 24:45.442
It doesn't make any sense to me either.

24:47.194 --> 24:48.570
Gwen?

24:50.572 --> 24:53.367
| made her a vow I would keep Arthur safe.

24:53.534 --> 24:55.703
You don't have to worry. I'll keep him safe.

24:56.412 --> 24:58.497
| made a vow, Merlin.

25:03.752 --> 25:05.295
You still think about her?

25:06.130 --> 25:07.297
No.

25:08.716 --> 25:13.429
Arthur's a better man than me.

25:17.016 --> 25:18.392
I'm sorry.

25:21.103 --> 25:22.855
Why?

25:23.939 --> 25:26.025
He loves her, and...

25:27.693 --> 25:29.445
...she's happy.

25:36.035 --> 25:39.371
| remember the guards
walking me to my door.

25:39.872 --> 25:43.959
And then...nothing.

25:44.209 --> 25:46.712
It's just a surface wound.
You were very lucky.

25:46.879 --> 25:50.632
Everyone talks about the coldness,
but I don't feel cold at all.

25:52.051 --> 25:54.344
You weren't attacked by the Dorocha, Gwen.

25:55.971 --> 25:57.598
Then what?

26:00.976 --> 26:02.227
Gaius?

26:03.103 --> 26:05.647
| fear someone wanted to do you harm.

26:06.106 --> 26:08.650
-Why?
-Don't know.

26:09.401 --> 26:11.570
Well, surely if they did,
they'd have done a better job.

26:11.737 --> 26:15.324
Maybe.
But cold-blooded murder is suspicious.

26:15.908 --> 26:19.244
Better to leave you to the Dorocha.

26:35.260 --> 26:37.012
[WIND GUSTING]

26:53.278 --> 26:54.571
[SHRIEKING]

26:54.738 --> 26:55.989
Lancelot!

27:05.082 --> 27:07.376
[SHOUTING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

27:12.089 --> 27:14.383
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

27:39.366 --> 27:40.742
It's all right.

27:41.994 --> 27:43.287
It's all right.

27:52.880 --> 27:56.133
-Thank you.
-Who is your friend?

27:57.593 --> 28:00.679
-I'm Lancelot.
GREAT DRAGON: Of course.

28:00.846 --> 28:06.018
Sir Lancelot. The bravest
and most noble of them all.

28:06.393 --> 28:09.897
-I'm not sure that's true.
GREAT DRAGON: We shall see.

28:10.063 --> 28:13.150
For now, there are
more pressing things at hand.

28:13.317 --> 28:16.945
The Dorocha cannot be allowed
to remain in this world.

28:17.112 --> 28:20.032
The sundered veil must be restored.

28:20.199 --> 28:23.785
We're on our way
to the Isle of the Blessed to help Arthur heal it.

28:23.952 --> 28:27.372
Indeed. But at what price?

28:28.040 --> 28:31.543
| know that the spirit world
demands a sacrifice.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.879
GREAT DRAGON:
It demands nothing.

28:34.046 --> 28:37.674
It is the Cailleach,
the gatekeeper to the spirit world...

28:37.841 --> 28:39.551
...who asks such a price.

28:39.718 --> 28:41.970
And there is no other way?

28:42.804 --> 28:44.890
There is not.

28:45.265 --> 28:48.268
Arthur intends to sacrifice himself
to heal the vell.

28:48.435 --> 28:52.105
It is my destiny to protect him.
You taught me that.

28:52.272 --> 28:56.818
Merlin, you must not do this.

28:58.278 --> 29:00.447
Then I have no choice.

29:01.573 --> 29:03.825
| must take his place.

29:04.785 --> 29:07.663
From the moment I met you...

29:07.829 --> 29:10.999
...| saw something that was invisible.

29:12.209 --> 29:17.506
Now it is there for all to see.

29:18.715 --> 29:23.637
A lot of what you see, old friend...

29:24.513 --> 29:26.640
...Is what you taught me.

29:26.807 --> 29:32.813
It will be an empty world without you,
young warlock.

29:44.283 --> 29:46.451
[WINGS FLAPPING]

30:03.093 --> 30:05.804
LANCELOT:
When we get to the Isle of the Blessed...

30:06.555 --> 30:09.099
...do you really intend to sacrifice yourself?

30:10.225 --> 30:11.768
MERLIN:
What do you want me to say?

30:11.935 --> 30:14.813
| look at you and I wonder about myself.

30:16.106 --> 30:19.443
Could I knowingly give up my life
for something?

30:20.944 --> 30:22.696
You have to have a reason.

30:23.864 --> 30:26.158
Something you care about.

30:26.908 --> 30:29.202
Something that's more
important than anything.

30:29.369 --> 30:30.996
Hyah.

30:31.705 --> 30:33.582
[HORSE WHINNIES]

30:39.921 --> 30:41.965
Looks like someone beat us to it.

30:42.132 --> 30:43.300
Bandits?

30:46.219 --> 30:48.221
Do you think we'll make it before nightfall?

30:48.388 --> 30:50.974
There's only one way to find out. Hyah!

31:01.860 --> 31:03.612
[GROANS]

31:06.114 --> 31:08.200
Has something died?

31:08.742 --> 31:11.995
-Why am I always the butt?
-Can't think.

31:13.413 --> 31:15.082
Pick on Percival.

31:15.248 --> 31:16.750
Why me?

31:16.917 --> 31:18.752
He washes.

31:19.294 --> 31:23.006
-And he doesn't set fire to his socks.
-Ah! No.

31:25.592 --> 31:26.635
[CLATTERING NEARBY]

31:26.802 --> 31:27.844
Quiet.

31:29.179 --> 31:30.680
[CLATTERING AND CLANGING]

31:43.360 --> 31:44.403
Lancelot?

31:45.612 --> 31:47.197
How's Merlin?

31:48.240 --> 31:50.117
Bad news.

31:52.536 --> 31:54.454
He's still alive.

31:58.083 --> 31:59.501
[CHUCKLES]

32:00.961 --> 32:02.796
ELYAN:
Merlin.

32:16.643 --> 32:19.229
-Good to see you, Merlin.
-Yeah.

32:19.396 --> 32:21.273
It's good to see you too.

32:29.614 --> 32:32.409
It's going to be fine.
Everything will be all right.

32:33.201 --> 32:34.870
I'm just tired.

32:42.794 --> 32:45.547
You don't have to sacrifice yourself.

32:47.382 --> 32:49.134
| have to save my people.

32:52.137 --> 32:54.389
| will take your place.

32:55.765 --> 32:56.808
Merlin--

32:56.975 --> 33:00.604
What is the life of a servant
compared to that of a prince?

33:01.855 --> 33:03.565
Well, a good servant's hard to come by.

33:04.149 --> 33:06.526
-I'm not that good.
-True.

33:14.284 --> 33:15.952
One thing.

33:16.328 --> 33:19.039
Look after Guinevere.
| want her to be happy in her life.

33:19.206 --> 33:21.166
She deserves that.

33:24.586 --> 33:27.214
Don't worry. I'll make sure.

33:44.022 --> 33:46.107
ARTHUR;:
The Isle of the Blessed.

33:55.367 --> 33:57.494
[CREATURE SCREECHING]

34:15.136 --> 34:16.179
[CREATURE SCREECHES]

34:16.346 --> 34:19.224
-What is that?
GWAINE: I really hope I'm wrong.

34:19.391 --> 34:21.976
[SCREECHING]

34:24.771 --> 34:26.063
Wyvern!

34:26.273 --> 34:27.815
[SCREECHING]

34:35.907 --> 34:36.992
ARTHUR:
You're right!

34:38.909 --> 34:40.661
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

34:46.208 --> 34:48.003
[SCREECHES]

34:56.511 --> 34:59.139
See? That's how you deal with them.

35:01.683 --> 35:03.059
We need to keep moving.

35:11.026 --> 35:12.277
[SCREECHING]

35:12.444 --> 35:15.447
LEON:
Sire, you must go on. We'll fend them off.

35:17.240 --> 35:18.533
Good luck.

35:43.933 --> 35:47.479
CAILLEACH:
It is not often we have visitors.

35:53.568 --> 35:55.612
Put an end to this.

35:56.363 --> 35:59.574
| demand you heal the tear
between the two worlds.

35:59.741 --> 36:02.243
It was not I who created this horror.

36:02.410 --> 36:04.579
Why should it be I that stops it?

36:05.664 --> 36:08.333
Because innocent people are dying.

36:08.792 --> 36:10.585
Indeed.

36:10.794 --> 36:12.671
[LAUGHS]

36:14.547 --> 36:15.632
[YELLS]

36:18.843 --> 36:20.595
[GRUNTS]

36:22.347 --> 36:24.599
Is this the best you can do?

36:25.809 --> 36:27.811
| know what you want.

36:28.436 --> 36:29.854
Do you?

36:32.399 --> 36:35.360
And are you willing to let me have it?

36:38.238 --> 36:41.241
I'm prepared to pay
whatever price is necessary.

37:01.886 --> 37:03.221
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

37:29.664 --> 37:32.500
So, Emrys...

37:33.376 --> 37:36.671
...you choose to challenge me after all.

37:46.931 --> 37:50.935
Will you give yourself to the spirits
to save your prince?

37:51.811 --> 37:54.063
It is my destiny.

37:54.564 --> 37:56.232
Perhaps.

37:58.943 --> 38:01.029
But your time among men
is not yet over, Emrys...

38:01.196 --> 38:03.156
...even if you want it to be.

38:07.243 --> 38:08.912
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

38:15.710 --> 38:18.254
[VOICES SCREAMING]

38:26.429 --> 38:28.389
No! No!

38:30.642 --> 38:32.143
No!

38:35.563 --> 38:37.065
No.

38:41.945 --> 38:43.363
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

39:05.093 --> 39:07.762
ARTHUR:
| want to pay tribute to Sir Lancelot.

39:09.764 --> 39:11.599
We owe him a great debt.

39:14.018 --> 39:16.938
It is not just his deed that we'll never forget.

39:19.190 --> 39:20.942
It is his courage...

39:22.777 --> 39:24.863
...his compassion...

39:26.531 --> 39:28.408
...his unselfish heart.

39:42.255 --> 39:44.632
He was the most noble knight I'll ever know.

39:46.384 --> 39:48.428
He gave his life for all of us.

40:25.673 --> 40:27.884
He didn't sacrifice himself for Camelot.

40:30.094 --> 40:33.222
| asked him to look after you,
and he promised me with his life.

40:38.394 --> 40:40.730
He was true to his word.

41:15.306 --> 41:16.349
[MORGANA SCREAMS]

41:16.516 --> 41:18.393
-Arthur was lucky.
-And Guinevere?

41:18.559 --> 41:21.020
-It was only by chance that Gaius found her.
-No, you're wrong.

41:21.187 --> 41:23.564
We were not thwarted by luck. It was Emrys.

41:23.731 --> 41:25.316
Emrys?

41:26.985 --> 41:28.903
The Cailleach warned me about him.

41:29.904 --> 41:33.074
She said he was my destiny and my doom.

41:34.409 --> 41:36.911
It was he that thwarted us. I'm sure of it.

41:37.078 --> 41:39.080
So, what's to be done?

41:40.498 --> 41:44.085
As long as he exists,
| will never gain what is rightfully mine.

41:52.176 --> 41:54.887
You must help me find this Emrys...

41:56.431 --> 41:58.266
...and destroy him.

42:08.026 --> 42:09.527
[DOOR OPENS]

42:10.153 --> 42:11.237
AGRAVAINE:
Gaius.

42:11.404 --> 42:13.322
GAIUS:
How can I be of assistance?

42:13.990 --> 42:16.200
You're a man of great
knowledge and wisdom.

42:16.367 --> 42:17.493
[GAIUS SCOFFS]

42:17.660 --> 42:19.454
GAIUS:
Knowledge perhaps.

42:20.288 --> 42:23.666
AGRAVAINE:
Have you ever come across a sorcerer...

42:23.833 --> 42:25.376
...called Emrys?

42:31.466 --> 42:34.510
No. Doesn't sound familiar.

42:34.719 --> 42:39.140
Hmm. Well, if you do hear mention
of the name...

42:39.807 --> 42:41.768
I'll be sure to tell you.

42:41.934 --> 42:44.145
AGRAVAINE:
It will not go unrewarded.

42:55.281 --> 42:58.618
There's only one person
could have heard that name.

42:59.118 --> 43:00.328
Morgana.

43:01.037 --> 43:04.499
We know her powers are growing.
She too must have seen the Cailleach.

43:05.208 --> 43:06.793
But Agravaine?

43:07.543 --> 43:10.797
| suspect he is not as virtuous as he seems.

43:10.963 --> 43:13.758
And don't forget,
he has every reason to despise Uther.

43:15.343 --> 43:17.303
We must beware, Merlin.

43:17.470 --> 43:22.809
Morgana can never know the truth.
She must never know who you really are.

43:26.854 --> 43:28.731
MALE VOICE:
Merlin.

43:30.066 --> 43:34.278
MAN: We must make sure this is a celebration
the young prince will never forget.

43:37.198 --> 43:38.282
You can't die.

43:38.449 --> 43:41.035
If you were me,
would you use magic to save his life?

43:41.202 --> 43:44.747
-Yes, I would. I would do whatever it took.
GAIUS: You can't risk exposing yourself.

43:44.914 --> 43:46.040
It's too dangerous.

43:46.207 --> 43:49.544
Do you think Uther is going to thank you
for healing him with magic?

43:49.710 --> 43:52.213
-If it works, I won't have to hide anymore.
-You.

44:32.587 --> 44:33.588
[English - US - SDH]
